<font color="#FF0000">WHAT MEMORIAL DAY IS ABOUT!</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26 14:51:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I cannot believe that so many have got wrong what this day is about! It is not about the Wall or any other memorials. It is not about us vets or them protestors. It is not about reflections on whether the Vietnam was right or wrong. It is not about anything except remembering those who gave the ultimate, those that DIED, while doing what this country ask of them. From the Civil War to the Spanish American War to WWI, WWII, Korea, Vietnam, the Gulf War and all the skirmishes in between. It is not for those that are living. It is for those that DIED. We surviving veterans have Veterans Day. Thoughts on the politics of any war has the rest of the year. This day belongs to those that DIED, those that DIED, those that DIED.............Honor and pay tribute to those that Died and the love ones they left behind!
<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


